00:46:42.150 --> 00:46:45.690
where we have
digitized and scaled up

00:46:45.690 --> 00:46:47.900
social interaction in
the form of social media,

00:46:47.900 --> 00:46:51.390
that every interaction you can
create in a social setting you

00:46:51.390 --> 00:46:53.634
can now make in a
digital, social setting.

00:46:53.634 --> 00:46:55.800
But one thing that we haven't
been able to digitize,

00:46:55.800 --> 00:46:57.216
and you can see
that this has been

00:46:57.216 --> 00:47:01.530
abused by state
actors and [INAUDIBLE]

00:47:01.530 --> 00:47:03.750
is the idea of digital trust.

00:47:03.750 --> 00:47:04.770
How do we create--

00:47:04.770 --> 00:47:08.250
how do I know that when
I engage on social media

00:47:08.250 --> 00:47:10.590
that the information
that's being given to me

00:47:10.590 --> 00:47:11.280
is trustworthy?

00:47:11.280 --> 00:47:13.930
How do I know who is at the
other end of the computer?

00:47:13.930 --> 00:47:17.760
And as a company,
I think, we have

00:47:17.760 --> 00:47:20.370
an interest in thinking
about how do we

00:47:20.370 --> 00:47:24.732
solve this general problem
of trust in the digital age?

00:47:24.732 --> 00:47:26.190
We have communities
that are small,

00:47:26.190 --> 00:47:28.530
but we are trying
to build platforms

00:47:28.530 --> 00:47:30.510
that can connect us globally.

00:47:30.510 --> 00:47:33.810
In order to do that, we need
some sort of digital platform.

00:47:33.810 --> 00:47:36.690
So my question to you
is how do we build trust

00:47:36.690 --> 00:47:41.660
in a digital realm, and how do
we establish as an organization

00:47:41.660 --> 00:47:45.849
that remote digital
form of trust?

